<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880129-0162 </DOCNO><HL> Dividend News: Alexander andamp; Baldwin Proposes 2-for-1 Split </HL><SO> </SO><CO> ALEX </CO><IN> DIV </IN><DATELINE> HONOLULU  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Alexander andamp; Baldwin Inc. said its board authorized a 2-for-1 split of common stock, subject to holders' approval of a proposal to increase authorized shares.    The transportation, sugar and property development concern also said it intended to raise its quarterly cash dividend by 18% in the second quarter of 1988. For the first quarter, the company will make its usual 34-cents-a-share payout March 3 to stock of record Feb. 11.    Alexander andamp; Baldwin, which currently has 25,175,000 shares outstanding, said it will ask holders to approve an increase in authorized shares to 150 million from the 45 million currently authorized. If approved, the company would proceed with a stock split for stock of record May 12. The new cash dividend would be 20 cents a share for each post-split share, and would be paid June 2. </TEXT></DOC>